{"TopicId":175648,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"Stock SSTO mission to an Exoplanet","CreatedByName":"JacobJHC","CreatedById":152333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-05T20:17:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JacobJHC","CreatedById":152333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-05T20:17:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI always thought that with the use of ions and gravity assist that an exoplanet mission wasn\u0027t too far out of the question. So I gave it a try and...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/rryVzJCHR5Y?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBig thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156312-andrewdrawsprettypictures/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022156312\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/156312-andrewdrawsprettypictures/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AndrewDrawsPrettyPictures\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for making the Extrasolar system pack which is used to add the exoplanet into the game. You did a very good job with everything, from the design to the visual enhancements.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pipcard","CreatedById":2541,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T03:37:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long did it actually take?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JacobJHC","CreatedById":152333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T04:04:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223393901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528256239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pipcard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Pipcard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long did it actually take?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout 1690 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAgain","CreatedById":150764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T07:35:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223393922\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528257861\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JacobJHC\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JacobJHC said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout 1690 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EGlark.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s, uhh, amazing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T09:07:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose gravity assists, you used several of them... How do you plan those??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JacobJHC","CreatedById":152333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T13:04:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223394018\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528276043\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183478\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nivee~\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Nivee~ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose gravity assists, you used several of them... How do you plan those??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI either got lucky that the trajectory was going to line up or I timewarped until I got an encounter. When it comes to gravity assists patience is the key. Also Kerbal Alarm Clock tells me when certain launch windows are so that helps also.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T13:43:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223393922\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528257861\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JacobJHC\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, JacobJHC said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout 1690 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood gravy... That\u0027s a long time, very few things IRL would last that long, although that\u0027s only about 480 Earth years. Realistically, three things would have happened.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. The ship would stop working\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Kerbin would invent warp drives and rescue the crew of the mission before they got there (or home)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. They would land back on Kerbin and find a futuristic civilization\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. They would land back on Kerbin and find a post-apocalyptic wasteland and nobody on the planet would remember the mission\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T15:29:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223394148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528292613\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin would invent warp drives and rescue the crew of the mission before they got there (or home)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe crew of the mission would be very disappointed though...all their sacrifices and efforts in vain because some SmartS scientist invented the Warp Drive..... \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ENo matter what the outcome is, it will most probably lead to despair...\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JacobJHC","CreatedById":152333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-06T16:45:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223394205\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175648\u0022 data-ipsquote-